<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870304-0035 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Fruit of the Loom Inc.</HL><DD> 03/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> FTCBOND MARKET NEWS (BON)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)INITIAL STOCK OFFERINGS (INI) </IN><TEXT>   FRUIT OF THE LOOM INC. a Chicago-based apparel concern, said it completed two debt offerings consisting of $250 million of 10 3/4% senior notes due 1995 and $60 million of 6 3/4% convertible debentures due 2002. Both issues were priced at par, and the debentures are convertible into Class A common at $11.25 a share. The company also completed its initial offering of 27 million Class A common shares at $9 each. Proceeds will be used to reduce debt and for general corporate purposes. Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. was the chief underwriter for the issues. </TEXT></DOC>